Knowledge Musona has reacted with excitement after being offered a two-year contract by Saudi Arabian club, Al Tai Club, which campaigns in the Saudi Professional League, the top tier of Saudi football. The 31-year-old former Kaizer Chiefs star was unveiled by the club coached by Mohamed Kouki at the weekend. Musona, through his Twitter account, said: "I'm excited for my new chapter with Tai Club in Saudi Arabia. I would like to thank my former team R.S.C Anderlecht for the opportunity they gave me. I also wish to express my sincere gratitude to @kas_eupen for the wonderful two seasons we spent together." A statement from the Saudis club said: "The Zimbabwean player signed a two-year contract with Al-Taie, after passing the medical examination he conducted at Al-Ahly Medical Complex."